text: [Music]
I'm AJ Kang and I've worked at Amazon
Web Services for just over three and a
half years I'm a team leader and Account
Manager at AWS and essentially that
involves looking after a subset of
customers and helping them migrate over
to the cloud
I joined AWS because the leadership
principles after having done all the
research and seeing how well they were
expressed on a daily basis I was really
keen to come and join because of that
and since coming here I've seen them
demonstrated by you know all staff on a
daily basis and it's the reason why I'm
still here I prepared for my interview
by initially talking to the individual
who'd referred me took a look at the
leadership principles quite closely as
well as Glassdoor and a couple of
shareholder letters taking a look at the
reviews I've got a very good
understanding of what it takes to be an
amazonian and then really focus my
efforts on understanding the leadership
principles as best as possible people
should join AWS because this is truly a
career enhancing opportunity there's
such a great opportunity to get involved
in so many different areas that you will
never be bored not only will you become
very good at your current job and what's
out there you'll have the ability to
develop and pick up numerous different
skills if there's one word that would
sum up my time here at AWS it would be
enhancing I feel itself gained more
experience in three and a half years
than I had done for the previous 10
years of my career and I'd like to think
that I've also enhanced the business in
ways and helped it scale and grow
effectively
